<section class="py-24 px-4">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif text-[var(--color-heading)] mb-12">About the Project</h2>

    <div class="text-text-primary leading-relaxed font-sans text-lg space-y-6 text-left">
      <p>
        Every culture that has ever existed found its way to stillness. Desert hermits counting breaths on a rope. Chan monks pouring tea until the steam matched their breathing. Quakers sitting in silence until the light moved someone to speak. A Hasidic nigun hummed under curfew. This is not new. This is the oldest thing we know.
      </p>

      <p>
        The StillPoint Saga asks what happens when a species with that heritage — all of it, every tradition, every lineage — nearly forgets it. And what it looks like to remember. Three eras, spanning 2029 to 2095. Physicists and couriers, nine-year-olds and elders. Crisis, resistance, and the slow work of building something that isn't optimized for extraction.
      </p>

      <p>
        Published chapter by chapter as it's written. Free to read. A human-AI collaboration — the process mirrors the question the story asks.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
